Note:
Comprehensive Test Suite for Memory Allocator Visualization Module

Tests all functionality of the memory allocator visualization and debugging system including:
- Real-time allocator visualization and monitoring
- Memory allocation pattern analysis and visualization
- Debugging tools for allocator performance and behavior
- Visual representation of memory fragmentation and usage
- Interactive debugging and inspection capabilities
- Performance monitoring and metrics visualization
- Error detection and visualization for memory issues
- Production-ready debugging and monitoring tools
:End Note

Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/memory/allocator_visualization" as AllocatorViz
Import "../../../../../../src/stdlib/advanced/utilities/common" as Common

Note: Test Configuration Constants
Let TEST_ALLOCATOR_COUNT be 5
Let TEST_ALLOCATION_COUNT be 100
Let TEST_VISUALIZATION_WINDOW_MS be 1000
Let TEST_MEMORY_BLOCK_SIZE be 1024

Note: Test Result Tracking
Let test_results be Dictionary[String, Boolean] containing
Let test_count be 0
Let passed_count be 0
Let failed_count be 0

Note: Helper Functions for Testing

Process called "run_test" that takes test_name as String and test_function as Function returns Boolean:
    Set test_count to test_count plus 1
    
    Try:
        Display message "Running test: " plus test_name
        Let result be test_function()
        
        If result:
            Set passed_count to passed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to true
            Display message "  ✓ PASS: " plus test_name
        Otherwise:
            Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
            Set test_results[test_name] to false
            Display message "  ✗ FAIL: " plus test_name
            
        Return result
        
    Catch error:
        Set failed_count to failed_count plus 1
        Set test_results[test_name] to false
        Display message "  ✗ ERROR: " plus test_name plus " - " plus error.message
        Return false

Process called "assert_true" that takes condition as Boolean and message as String returns Boolean:
    If not condition:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_equal" that takes actual as Any and expected as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not equal to expected:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected: " plus expected
        Display message "    Actual: " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_greater_than" that takes actual as Float and threshold as Float and message as String returns Boolean:
    If actual is not greater than threshold:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Display message "    Expected > " plus threshold plus ", got " plus actual
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "assert_not_null" that takes value as Any and message as String returns Boolean:
    If value is null:
        Display message "    Assertion failed: " plus message
        Return false
    Return true

Process called "create_mock_allocator" that takes name as String and type as String returns AllocatorViz.MockAllocator:
    Return AllocatorViz.MockAllocator with:
        name as name
        allocator_type as type
        total_allocated as 0
        total_freed as 0
        current_usage as 0
        peak_usage as 0
        allocation_count as 0
        fragmentation_ratio as 0.0
        metadata as dictionary containing

Process called "create_mock_allocation" that takes size as Integer and address as Integer returns AllocatorViz.Allocation:
    Return AllocatorViz.Allocation with:
        size as size
        address as address
        timestamp as Common.get_current_time_ms()
        allocator_name as "test_allocator"
        status as "active"
        metadata as dictionary containing

Note: Unit Tests for Visualization Context Creation

Process called "test_create_visualization_context" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_config be AllocatorViz.VisualizationConfig with:
        update_interval_ms as 100
        history_window_ms as 5000
        enable_real_time as true
        enable_heat_map as true
        
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as viz_config
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as viz_context and message as "Visualization context should be created"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as viz_context.config.update_interval_ms and expected as 100 and message as "Update interval should be set correctly"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as viz_context.config.enable_real_time and message as "Real-time should be enabled"
    Let result4 be assert_not_null with value as viz_context.renderer and message as "Renderer should be initialized"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_register_allocator_for_visualization" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    Let test_allocator be create_mock_allocator with name as "test_arena" and type as "arena"
    
    Let registration_result be AllocatorViz.register_allocator with context as viz_context and allocator as test_allocator
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as registration_result and message as "Allocator registration should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (viz_context.tracked_allocators.length is equal to 1) and message as "Allocator should be tracked"
    Let result3 be assert_equal with actual as viz_context.tracked_allocators[0].name and expected as "test_arena" and message as "Allocator name should match"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_visualization_data_collection" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    Let test_allocator be create_mock_allocator with name as "data_collector" and type as "pool"
    
    AllocatorViz.register_allocator with context as viz_context and allocator as test_allocator
    
    Note: Simulate allocations
    For i from 0 to 9:
        Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as (i plus 1) multiplied by 64 and address as (i multiplied by 1000)
        AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
    
    Let viz_data be AllocatorViz.collect_visualization_data with context as viz_context
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as viz_data and message as "Visualization data should be collected"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as viz_data.allocation_count and expected as 10 and message as "Allocation count should match"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as viz_data.total_memory_used and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Total memory used should be positive"
    Let result4 be assert_not_null with value as viz_data.allocation_timeline and message as "Allocation timeline should be present"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Unit Tests for Real-time Monitoring

Process called "test_real_time_monitoring" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    Let monitor be AllocatorViz.create_real_time_monitor with context as viz_context
    
    Let start_result be AllocatorViz.start_monitoring with monitor as monitor
    
    Note: Simulate some activity
    For i from 0 to 4:
        Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as 256 and address as (i multiplied by 1000)
        AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
    
    Let monitoring_data be AllocatorViz.get_current_monitoring_data with monitor as monitor
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as start_result and message as "Monitoring should start successfully"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as monitor.is_running and message as "Monitor should be running"
    Let result3 be assert_not_null with value as monitoring_data and message as "Monitoring data should be available"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as monitoring_data.samples_collected and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Samples should be collected"
    
    AllocatorViz.stop_monitoring with monitor as monitor
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_memory_usage_heatmap" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    
    Note: Create memory map with various allocations
    For i from 0 to 19:
        Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as 128 and address as (i multiplied by 128)
        AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
    
    Let heatmap be AllocatorViz.generate_memory_heatmap with context as viz_context
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as heatmap and message as "Heatmap should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as heatmap.resolution and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Heatmap resolution should be positive"
    Let result3 be assert_not_null with value as heatmap.color_data and message as "Color data should be present"
    Let result4 be assert_equal with actual as heatmap.allocation_blocks and expected as 20 and message as "Allocation blocks should match"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_fragmentation_visualization" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    
    Note: Create fragmented memory pattern
    For i from 0 to 9:
        If i modulo 2 is equal to 0:
            Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as 64 and address as (i multiplied by 256)
            AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
        Otherwise:
            Note: Create gap (free space)
            AllocatorViz.record_free_space with context as viz_context and address as (i multiplied by 256) and size as 64
    
    Let fragmentation_viz be AllocatorViz.visualize_fragmentation with context as viz_context
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as fragmentation_viz and message as "Fragmentation visualization should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as fragmentation_viz.fragmentation_ratio and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Fragmentation ratio should be positive"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as fragmentation_viz.free_blocks and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Free blocks should be detected"
    Let result4 be assert_not_null with value as fragmentation_viz.visual_representation and message as "Visual representation should be present"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Unit Tests for Interactive Debugging

Process called "test_interactive_memory_inspector" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    Let inspector be AllocatorViz.create_memory_inspector with context as viz_context
    
    Note: Create test memory layout
    For i from 0 to 9:
        Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as (i plus 1) multiplied by 32 and address as (i multiplied by 1000)
        AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
    
    Let inspection_result be AllocatorViz.inspect_memory_range with inspector as inspector and start_address as 0 and end_address as 10000
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as inspection_result and message as "Memory inspection should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as inspection_result.allocations_found and expected as 10 and message as "All allocations should be found"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as inspection_result.total_memory_inspected and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Memory inspected should be positive"
    Let result4 be assert_not_null with value as inspection_result.detailed_layout and message as "Detailed layout should be provided"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_allocation_lifecycle_tracking" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    Let lifecycle_tracker be AllocatorViz.create_lifecycle_tracker with context as viz_context
    
    Note: Create allocation and track its lifecycle
    Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as 512 and address as 5000
    AllocatorViz.track_allocation_lifecycle with tracker as lifecycle_tracker and allocation as allocation
    
    Note: Simulate allocation usage
    AllocatorViz.record_allocation_access with tracker as lifecycle_tracker and address as 5000 and access_type as "read"
    AllocatorViz.record_allocation_access with tracker as lifecycle_tracker and address as 5000 and access_type as "write"
    
    Note: Simulate deallocation
    AllocatorViz.record_deallocation with tracker as lifecycle_tracker and address as 5000
    
    Let lifecycle_data be AllocatorViz.get_lifecycle_data with tracker as lifecycle_tracker and address as 5000
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as lifecycle_data and message as "Lifecycle data should be available"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as lifecycle_data.access_count and expected as 2 and message as "Access count should match"
    Let result3 be assert_true with condition as lifecycle_data.was_deallocated and message as "Deallocation should be recorded"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as lifecycle_data.lifetime_ms and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Lifetime should be positive"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Unit Tests for Performance Visualization

Process called "test_allocation_performance_metrics" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    Let perf_monitor be AllocatorViz.create_performance_monitor with context as viz_context
    
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    
    Note: Simulate allocations with timing
    For i from 0 to 19:
        Let allocation_start be Common.get_current_time_ms()
        Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as 256 and address as (i multiplied by 1000)
        Let allocation_end be Common.get_current_time_ms()
        
        AllocatorViz.record_allocation_timing with monitor as perf_monitor and allocation as allocation and duration_ms as (allocation_end minus allocation_start)
    
    Let performance_metrics be AllocatorViz.get_performance_metrics with monitor as perf_monitor
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as performance_metrics and message as "Performance metrics should be available"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as performance_metrics.total_allocations and expected as 20 and message as "Total allocations should match"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as performance_metrics.average_allocation_time_ms and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Average allocation time should be positive"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as performance_metrics.throughput_per_second and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Throughput should be positive"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_memory_pressure_visualization" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    
    Note: Simulate increasing memory pressure
    For pressure_level from 1 to 10:
        For i from 0 to (pressure_level minus 1):
            Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as (pressure_level multiplied by 64) and address as ((pressure_level multiplied by 1000) plus i)
            AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
        
        AllocatorViz.record_memory_pressure with context as viz_context and pressure_level as (pressure_level multiplied by 0.1)
    
    Let pressure_viz be AllocatorViz.visualize_memory_pressure with context as viz_context
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as pressure_viz and message as "Memory pressure visualization should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_greater_than with actual as pressure_viz.peak_pressure and threshold as 0.5 and message as "Peak pressure should be significant"
    Let result3 be assert_not_null with value as pressure_viz.pressure_timeline and message as "Pressure timeline should be present"
    Let result4 be assert_greater_than with actual as pressure_viz.pressure_events and threshold as 5.0 and message as "Multiple pressure events should be recorded"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Unit Tests for Debugging Tools

Process called "test_memory_leak_detection_visualization" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    Let leak_detector be AllocatorViz.create_leak_detector with context as viz_context
    
    Note: Create allocations without corresponding deallocations (potential leaks)
    For i from 0 to 4:
        Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as 128 and address as (i multiplied by 1000)
        AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
    
    Note: Only deallocate some allocations
    For i from 0 to 1:
        AllocatorViz.record_deallocation with context as viz_context and address as (i multiplied by 1000) and size as 128
    
    Let leak_analysis be AllocatorViz.analyze_potential_leaks with detector as leak_detector
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as leak_analysis and message as "Leak analysis should be performed"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as leak_analysis.potential_leaks and expected as 3 and message as "Potential leaks should be detected"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as leak_analysis.leaked_memory_bytes and threshold as 0.0 and message as "Leaked memory should be calculated"
    Let result4 be assert_not_null with value as leak_analysis.leak_visualization and message as "Leak visualization should be generated"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Process called "test_allocation_pattern_analysis" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    Let pattern_analyzer be AllocatorViz.create_pattern_analyzer with context as viz_context
    
    Note: Create different allocation patterns
    Note: Sequential pattern
    For i from 0 to 9:
        Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as 64 and address as (i multiplied by 64)
        AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
    
    Note: Random pattern
    For i from 0 to 9:
        Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as 128 and address as (i multiplied by 317) modulo 10000
        AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
    
    Let pattern_analysis be AllocatorViz.analyze_allocation_patterns with analyzer as pattern_analyzer
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as pattern_analysis and message as "Pattern analysis should be performed"
    Let result2 be assert_not_null with value as pattern_analysis.detected_patterns and message as "Patterns should be detected"
    Let result3 be assert_greater_than with actual as pattern_analysis.pattern_confidence and threshold as 0.5 and message as "Pattern confidence should be reasonable"
    Let result4 be assert_not_null with value as pattern_analysis.pattern_visualization and message as "Pattern visualization should be generated"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Performance Tests

Process called "test_visualization_performance" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    Let start_time be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    
    Note: Create large number of allocations to test performance
    For i from 0 to 999:
        Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as 64 and address as (i multiplied by 64)
        AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
    
    Let viz_generation_start be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    Let viz_data be AllocatorViz.collect_visualization_data with context as viz_context
    Let viz_generation_end be Common.get_current_time_ms()
    
    Let total_time_ms be viz_generation_end minus start_time
    Let viz_generation_time_ms be viz_generation_end minus viz_generation_start
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as viz_data and message as "Visualization data should be generated"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (viz_generation_time_ms is less than 100.0) and message as "Visualization generation should be fast"
    Let result3 be assert_equal with actual as viz_data.allocation_count and expected as 1000 and message as "All allocations should be processed"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_real_time_update_performance" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    Let monitor be AllocatorViz.create_real_time_monitor with context as viz_context
    
    AllocatorViz.start_monitoring with monitor as monitor
    
    Let update_times be list containing
    
    Note: Test multiple updates
    For i from 0 to 49:
        Let update_start be Common.get_current_time_ms()
        
        Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as 64 and address as (i multiplied by 100)
        AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
        AllocatorViz.update_real_time_display with monitor as monitor
        
        Let update_end be Common.get_current_time_ms()
        Let update_times be update_times with (update_end minus update_start) added
    
    AllocatorViz.stop_monitoring with monitor as monitor
    
    Let average_update_time be (sum of update_times) divided by (length of update_times)
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (average_update_time is less than 5.0) and message as "Average update time should be fast"
    Let result2 be assert_equal with actual as (length of update_times) and expected as 50 and message as "All updates should be measured"
    
    Return result1 and result2

Note: Error Handling Tests

Process called "test_invalid_visualization_data_handling" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    
    Note: Test with null allocation
    Let null_result be AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as null
    
    Note: Test with invalid allocation data
    Let invalid_allocation be AllocatorViz.Allocation with:
        size as -100
        address as -1000
        timestamp as -1.0
        allocator_name as ""
        status as "invalid"
        metadata as null
    
    Let invalid_result be AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as invalid_allocation
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as (not null_result) and message as "Null allocation should be rejected"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as (not invalid_result) and message as "Invalid allocation should be rejected"
    Let result3 be assert_not_null with value as AllocatorViz.get_last_error() and message as "Error should be recorded"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Process called "test_visualization_context_recovery" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    
    Note: Simulate context corruption
    AllocatorViz.simulate_context_corruption with context as viz_context
    
    Note: Attempt recovery
    Let recovery_result be AllocatorViz.recover_visualization_context with context as viz_context
    
    Let result1 be assert_true with condition as recovery_result and message as "Context recovery should succeed"
    Let result2 be assert_true with condition as viz_context.is_healthy and message as "Context should be healthy after recovery"
    Let result3 be assert_not_null with value as viz_context.renderer and message as "Renderer should be restored"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3

Note: Integration Tests

Process called "test_end_to_end_visualization_workflow" returns Boolean:
    Let viz_context be AllocatorViz.create_visualization_context with config as AllocatorViz.default_config
    Let test_allocator be create_mock_allocator with name as "e2e_allocator" and type as "hybrid"
    
    Note: Register allocator
    AllocatorViz.register_allocator with context as viz_context and allocator as test_allocator
    
    Note: Start monitoring
    Let monitor be AllocatorViz.create_real_time_monitor with context as viz_context
    AllocatorViz.start_monitoring with monitor as monitor
    
    Note: Perform various allocations
    For i from 0 to 19:
        Let allocation be create_mock_allocation with size as (i plus 1) multiplied by 32 and address as (i multiplied by 1000)
        AllocatorViz.record_allocation with context as viz_context and allocation as allocation
    
    Note: Generate all visualizations
    Let viz_data be AllocatorViz.collect_visualization_data with context as viz_context
    Let heatmap be AllocatorViz.generate_memory_heatmap with context as viz_context
    Let fragmentation_viz be AllocatorViz.visualize_fragmentation with context as viz_context
    Let performance_metrics be AllocatorViz.get_performance_metrics with monitor as monitor
    
    AllocatorViz.stop_monitoring with monitor as monitor
    
    Let result1 be assert_not_null with value as viz_data and message as "Visualization data should be complete"
    Let result2 be assert_not_null with value as heatmap and message as "Heatmap should be generated"
    Let result3 be assert_not_null with value as fragmentation_viz and message as "Fragmentation visualization should be generated"
    Let result4 be assert_not_null with value as performance_metrics and message as "Performance metrics should be available"
    
    Return result1 and result2 and result3 and result4

Note: Test Runner

Process called "run_all_allocator_visualization_tests" returns Dictionary[String, Any]:
    Display "Starting Allocator Visualization comprehensive test suite..."
    
    Note: Visualization Context Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_create_visualization_context" and test_function as test_create_visualization_context
    run_test with test_name as "test_register_allocator_for_visualization" and test_function as test_register_allocator_for_visualization
    run_test with test_name as "test_visualization_data_collection" and test_function as test_visualization_data_collection
    
    Note: Real-time Monitoring Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_real_time_monitoring" and test_function as test_real_time_monitoring
    run_test with test_name as "test_memory_usage_heatmap" and test_function as test_memory_usage_heatmap
    run_test with test_name as "test_fragmentation_visualization" and test_function as test_fragmentation_visualization
    
    Note: Interactive Debugging Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_interactive_memory_inspector" and test_function as test_interactive_memory_inspector
    run_test with test_name as "test_allocation_lifecycle_tracking" and test_function as test_allocation_lifecycle_tracking
    
    Note: Performance Visualization Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_allocation_performance_metrics" and test_function as test_allocation_performance_metrics
    run_test with test_name as "test_memory_pressure_visualization" and test_function as test_memory_pressure_visualization
    
    Note: Debugging Tools Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_memory_leak_detection_visualization" and test_function as test_memory_leak_detection_visualization
    run_test with test_name as "test_allocation_pattern_analysis" and test_function as test_allocation_pattern_analysis
    
    Note: Performance Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_visualization_performance" and test_function as test_visualization_performance
    run_test with test_name as "test_real_time_update_performance" and test_function as test_real_time_update_performance
    
    Note: Error Handling Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_invalid_visualization_data_handling" and test_function as test_invalid_visualization_data_handling
    run_test with test_name as "test_visualization_context_recovery" and test_function as test_visualization_context_recovery
    
    Note: Integration Tests
    run_test with test_name as "test_end_to_end_visualization_workflow" and test_function as test_end_to_end_visualization_workflow
    
    Display "Allocator Visualization test suite completed."
    Display "Results: " plus passed_count plus " passed, " plus failed_count plus " failed, " plus test_count plus " total"
    
    Return Dictionary[String, Any] with:
        "total_tests" as test_count
        "passed_tests" as passed_count
        "failed_tests" as failed_count
        "success_rate" as (passed_count divided by test_count)
        "test_results" as test_results

Note: Main execution
Process called "main":
    Let results be run_all_allocator_visualization_tests()
    Return results

Note: Execute tests when module is run
Let main_result be main()